                     </persName>
                     
                  , in his dwelling-house
            </rs>, <rs id="t17720429-18-cd98" type="crimeDate">March the 11th</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17720429-18-off97 t17720429-18-cd98"></join>. +</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17720429-18-person218">
                  Joseph
                   Weston
               <interp inst="t17720429-18-person218" type="surname" value="Weston"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17720429-18-person218" type="given" value="Joseph"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17720429-18-person218" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am servant to Mr. Bradley, a <rs id="t17720429-18-viclabel99" type="occupation">pawn-broker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17720429-18-victim217 t17720429-18-viclabel99"></join>, at the corner of <placeName id="t17720429-18-crimeloc100">Round-court, in the Strand</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17720429-18-crimeloc100" type="placeName" value="Round-court, in the Strand"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17720429-18-crimeloc100" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17720429-18-off97 t17720429-18-crimeloc100"></join>. On the 11th of March, between eight and nine o'clock in the evening, I observed that the case-door of the inside of the shop-window was broke open, and that the things mentioned in the indictment were stolen: they were advertised, in consequence of which some of them were stopped by 
               <persName id="t17720429-18-person219">
                  Moses
                   Levi
               <interp inst="t17720429-18-person219" type="surname" value="Levi"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17720429-18-person219" type="given" value="Moses"></interp>
